           <p style=3D"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 30px; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0;">Welcome back to Dry Powder.=
 I=E2=80=99m <b>Bill Cohan</b>.<br/><br/>The X valuation delusion continues=
=2E Earlier this week, it was reported=20=
that Fidelity, the enormous Boston-bas=
ed asset management firm that invested in X as part of <b>Elon Musk</b>=E2=
=80=99s takeover, marked <i>up</i> the value of its stake by 32 percent in =
October. That=E2=80=99s after Fidelity had written <i>down </i>the value of=
 its X investment by nearly 80 percent since the deal closed, in 2022. Nowa=
days, Fidelity values its investment in X at 72 percent less than it paid. =
Still not great.<br/><br/>I think it=E2=80=99s pretty clear by now that the=
 $31 billion of equity that Musk used to buy Twitter for $44 billion=E2=80=
=94$24 billion of which came from Elon, himself=E2=80=94is all but wiped ou=
t. Indeed, when the $13 billion of debt on the company would likely trade f=
or around 50 cents on the dollar, you can=E2=80=99t expect
that the equity will see much, if any, recovery, absent some Hail Mary-type=
 turnaround=E2=80=A6 such as, perhaps, a meme-stock merger with <b>Donald T=
rump</b>=E2=80=99s Truth Social. A little more on <i>that</i> tantalizing p=
rospect, below the fold.<br/><br/><i>But first=E2=80=A6</i><br/><br/></p><u=
l style=3D"margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:16px;line-height:30px;margin-to=
p:0;margin-bottom:0;list-style-type:square;mso-special-format:bullet"><li><=
i>Nathanson=E2=80=99s linear warning</i>: We all know that the cable busine=
ss is, and has been, in a distressing and inexorable state of free fall. An=
d few observers of this phenomenon are more astute than MoffettNathanson an=
alyst <b>Michael Nathanson</b>, whom my partner <b>John Ourand </b>intervie=
wed on his excellent <i><u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpb=
F9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUbEVjZGtOX1hNal84cDJlWUhZYz0iLCJocmVmIjoi=
